<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-04-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <head>581. Telegram 1799 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d581fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/4–1956. Secret.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-04-19">April 19, 1956, 6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d581-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d581-1"/>
                        <p>1799. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Comments todays meeting.</p>
                        <p><persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName>’s reactions to our second
                            revision draft about as expected and probably will forecast line he will
                            take at next meeting.</p>
                        <p>If at next meeting he flatly rejects our revision would propose, in
                            addition repeating as necessary arguments already made, stress his
                            responsibility offer alternative language which would meet our minimum
                            criteria of: (a) obviating possibility distortion declaration into
                            renunciation by United States its position re self-defense and (b) make
                            explicit renunciation of force applicable Taiwan area as well as
                            elsewhere.</p>
                        <p>Would appreciate Department’s comments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>